			<description><![CDATA[<p>
As a Mobile Product Manager at HootSuite, you will work with teams to deliver specific product initiatives designed to achieve specific business goals. You will build products from existing product ideas, and help to develop new ideas based on interactions with other product development team members, other business units, customers and your solid familiarity with the competitive product landscape.</p>
<p>
You must possess both strong business sense and in-depth technical knowledge about how mobile and web software works. You also have the ability to envision what a mobile product solution looks like and the skills to work with a team to make that vision a reality. You are an excellent communicator and leader who is comfortable interacting with any and all product stakeholders, technical or nontechnical.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Drive the mobile product development cycle and contribute to the strategic mobile direction as it fits within the broader HootSuite product roadmap</li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Meet regularly with multiple business units to understand and articulate mobile product requirements necessary to achieving business unit&nbsp; objectives</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Have the ability to assimilate and synthesize multiple inputs for possible product direction into a set of priorities based on existing business goals and company strategy</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Define and author product initiative requirements briefs that include key&nbsp; success metrics to be used by product development teams in the implementation and delivery of product initiatives</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Work with an engineering manager counterpart, provide leadership and product direction to teams working on specific product initiatives</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Collaborate with product and user interface designers to generate mobile user&nbsp; experiences that achieve product business objectives</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Work with product quality control teams to ensure that shipped products include the functionality required to meet business objectives</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Stay current and knowledgeable about mobile and web products that are competitive to HootSuite</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Provide visibility into mobile product development initiatives by communicating with the product marketing team and other&nbsp; non-technical HootSuite business about upcoming product releases and the value that those releases provide to customers</span></li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Required Skills &amp; Experience:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">A post-secondary degree, in computer science, business and/or engineering or equivalent work experience</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">4+ years of mobile internet product management experience</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Experience with iOS or Android apps and the mechanics of the Apple iStore and Google Play store</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">A track record for rapidly developing and releasing mobile features</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Knowledgeable about how large scale web applications work technologically</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">A deep understanding of social media and the social media marketplace</span></li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong><span style="font-size: 12px;">Bonus Assets:&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Familiarity with SDLC, agile methodologies, scrum, kanban</li>
<li>
Strong interest in social media</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
